I had assumed that it only looks at the edges and weights in the dot file when generating the lookup table. @{557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd} will probably know more about this.

In any case, I think the existing dat file will work fine. I also tried generating the 3 simple worlds using the updated script and found that the dot files are the same. So I don’t think we need to rengerate dat files for them too
